      <head>Violin family</head>

      <div>

        <p><figure>
            <head>Valerie Violin, Karl, and Eva, c. 1921 (Diana Windsor)</head>
            <graphic url="ViolinValKarlEva.jpg" xmt:type="thumb-caption" rend="left-img"
              width="150px" height="113px" mimeType="image/jpeg"/>
            <graphic url="ViolinValKarlEva.jpg" xmt:type="full" rend="left-img" width="800px"
              height="600px" mimeType="image/jpeg"/>
            <figDesc>Photograph of Valerie Violin with her children.</figDesc>
          </figure></p>
        <p>Viennese Jewish family, intimately connected with Heinrich and Jeanette Schenker through
          a friendship going back, in the case of Moriz and Heinrich, to 1896. </p>

        <p><hi rend="bold">Grandparental generation:</hi><list type="ordered">
            <item><ref cRef="entity-008353">Karl Violin [snr]</ref></item>
            <item><ref cRef="entity-008352">Juli Genovefa Violin (<hi rend="italic">n√©e</hi>
                Kohn)</ref></item>
          </list>
        </p>

        <p><hi rend="bold">Parental generation:</hi><list type="ordered">
            <item><ref cRef="entity-000913">Moriz Violin (Floriz)</ref></item>
            <item><ref cRef="entity-000914">Valerie Violin (Wally)</ref></item>
          </list>
        </p>

        <p><hi rend="bold">Children:</hi><list type="ordered">
            <item><ref cRef="entity-000912">Karl Violin (Karli)</ref></item>
            <item><ref cRef="entity-000911">Genovefa Violin (Eva)</ref></item>
          </list>
        </p>

        <p><hi rend="bold">Moriz's siblings:</hi><list>
            <item><ref cRef="entity-000908">Eduard Violin</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-000910">wife,
                Josefine</ref></item>
            <item><ref cRef="entity-008350">Nina Violin</ref></item>
            <item><ref cRef="entity-000909">Fanny Violin</ref></item>
            <item>and three others who died in childhood.</item>
          </list>
        </p>
      </div>


